Female.
Body color like male. Ventrite V deeply emarginate at apex, with longitudinal slender blade-shaped projection at midline (Fig. 
15C
) (male with ventrite V entirely convex and rounded). Proximal sclerites of bursa copulatrix oval, apex acute (Fig. 
14H
): base with without concavity, each with 14-16 large spines occupying two-thirds of edges, 9-10 smaller spines on disc.
